      "source": [
        "# K-Center From Scratch\n",
        "\n",
        "This Jupyter Notebook provides a detailed, step-by-step guide on implementing the K-Center clustering algorithm from scratch. It covers the following key areas:\n",
        "- Sample data points\n",
        "- Select one initial cluster center\n",
        "- Update distance of each point to its closest center\n",
        "- Add a new cluster center\n",
        "- Show clutering results"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "![Reference_Ch3_part_1_kcenters_from_scratch.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ],

      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HgYFWuQwTV8q"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import random\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "cmap = plt.get_cmap('tab10')\n",
        "colors = [cmap(i) for i in range(cmap.N)]\n",
        "\n",
        "mpl.rcParams[\"font.size\"] = 24\n",
        "mpl.rcParams[\"lines.linewidth\"] = 2\n",
        "\n",
        "seed = 0\n",
        "random.seed(seed)\n",
        "np.random.seed(seed)\n",
        "n_samples = 10\n",
        "markersize = 100"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Pjeg7wWYTV8s"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Sample data points"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZwgFQrwWTV8u"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "m1 = [1, 1]\n",
        "cov1 = [[1, 0], [0, 1]]\n",
        "s1 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m1, cov1, 5)\n",
        "\n",
        "m2 = [-1, -1]\n",
        "cov2 = [[1, -0.5], [-0.5, 1]]\n",
        "s2 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m2, cov2, 5)\n",
        "\n",
        "samples = np.concat([s1, s2])\n",
        "np.random.shuffle(samples)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {

        "plt.axis(\"equal\")"
      ]

        "## Select one initial cluster center"

    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wbnAq_uATV8y"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# initialize 1st center\n",
        "centers = [0, ]\n",
        "\n",
        "# initialize distance matrix\n",
        "losses = []\n",
        "n_points = samples.shape[0]\n",
        "distances = np.full(n_points, np.inf)"
      ]
    },

      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {

      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",
        "plt.scatter(samples[:, 0], samples[:, 1], s=markersize, color=\"k\")\n",
        "plt.scatter(samples[centers][:,0], samples[centers][:, 1],\n",
        "            s=markersize*3, c=colors[:len(centers)], marker=(5, 1))\n",
        "plt.axis(\"equal\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TS53dwiQTV8z"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Update distance of each point to its closest center"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MxRfk-ZjTV80"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "last_center = centers[-1]\n",
        "for i in range(n_points):\n",
        "    new_dist = np.linalg.norm(samples[i]-samples[last_center])\n",
        "    distances[i] = min(distances[i], new_dist)"
      ]
    },

        "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",

    {

      "metadata": {

      },
      "source": [
        "## Add a new cluster center"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "PBA4iCncTV82"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "## pick the point with the maximum distance as next center\n",
        "next_center = np.argmax(distances)\n",
        "centers.append(next_center)"
      ]
    },

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pbgckRVuTV84"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Show clutering results"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cfmmsltOTV84"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def k_center(points, k):\n",
        "    losses = []\n",
        "    n_points = points.shape[0]\n",
        "    centers = []\n",
        "    distances = np.full(n_points, np.inf)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for j in range(0, k):\n",
        "        if j == 0:\n",
        "            centers = [0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        for i in range(n_points):\n",
        "            new_dist = np.linalg.norm(points[i]-points[centers[-1]])\n",
        "            distances[i] = min(distances[i], new_dist)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if j>=1:\n",
        "            next_center = np.argmax(distances)\n",
        "            centers.append(next_center)\n",
        "\n",
        "        losses.append(np.max(distances))\n",
        "\n",
        "    return centers, losses"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pCsbz5SbTV85"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "k = 3\n",
        "new_centers, losses = k_center(samples, k)\n",
        "new_centers = samples[new_centers]"
      ]
